# .gitattributes
# BLUEPRINT: Composer 2 implements from this structure
# PURPOSE: Git attribute configuration. Sets line endings, merge strategies for queue CSV files
#          (prevent auto-merge corruption), and linguist overrides for GitHub language detection.
#          Per spec §26.12 item 341.
# SECTIONS:
#   - Global defaults: consistent line endings
#   - Python files: LF line endings enforced
#   - Shell scripts: LF line endings, executable bit
#   - Windows scripts: CRLF line endings
#   - YAML/JSON/TOML: LF line endings
#   - Queue CSV: union merge strategy (never auto-merge; conflicts must be resolved manually)
#   - Linguist overrides: mark generated docs and skills as non-primary language
# DESIGN DECISIONS:
#   - eol=lf for most files: consistent cross-platform behavior
#   - queue/*.csv uses merge=union: on conflict, include all lines from both sides (safer than auto-merge dropping rows)
#   - run `git config merge.union.driver true` to enable the union merge driver
#   - Linguist overrides prevent skills/ and prompts/ from dominating the language bar

# Default
* text=auto eol=lf

# Python source
*.py text eol=lf

# Shell scripts (force LF even on Windows checkout)
*.sh text eol=lf

# Windows batch files (CRLF required for Windows cmd.exe)
*.bat text eol=crlf

# Markup and config
*.md text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.ini text eol=lf
*.cfg text eol=lf
*.txt text eol=lf
*.rst text eol=lf

# Queue CSV: union merge to prevent row loss on concurrent edits
# This means conflicts include all rows from both sides — resolve manually
queue/*.csv merge=union text eol=lf

# Binary files: no line ending normalization
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.svg binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.pyc binary

# Linguist overrides for GitHub language detection
# Skills and prompts are Markdown but should not dominate the language bar
skills/** linguist-documentation=true
prompts/** linguist-documentation=true
docs/** linguist-documentation=true
*.md linguist-detectable=false
